In Sextum Pompeium civile bellum renovantem.

That this is an nHegory is clear3 and it is quoted as such by Quintilian, VIII. vx. 44. That it is (in part) an imitation of Almus, Fraym. 18, is also clear3 but whether it is rightly referred to Pompeius (as in the title,) or to what conjunctum of events it does belong, is and must be doubtful.
